le=\"word-break: break-word;\">We process personal data for the purpose of verifying the identity of the complainant and confirming the complaint.</span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">3.Provide of goods or service<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">We process personal data for provide service, contents, and payment / calculation.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">4.Apply in marketing and advertising<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">We process personal data for providing services according to demographic characteristics, posting advertisements, and verifying the validity of services.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Acticle 2(Processing and retention period of personal information)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&lt; sususoft &gt;We process and retain personal information within the period of retention and use of personal information in accordance with laws and regulations or within the period of retention and use of personal information agreed upon when collecting personal information from the information subject. Each personal information processing and retention period is as follows.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">• &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;Provide goods and service&gt;<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">• &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;Providing goods or services&gt; is related to retained and used for the above purpose from the date of consent for collection and use until &lt;5 years&gt;.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">• &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Retention Evidence: Retention and maintenance for refund and confirmation of personal information in response to inquiries<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">• &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Relevant laws:<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">1) Records on collection/processing and use of credit information : 3 years<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">2) Records of consumer complaints or dispute resolution : 3 years<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">3) Records of payment and supply service of goods: 5 years<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">4) Records of cancelation for contact or subscription: 5 years<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">5) Record of display/advertisment : 6 month<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Reason for exception :<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 3 (Rights and duties of Information Subjects and Legal Representatives and method of exercise)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">1.The information subject can exercise the right to view, correct, delete, and suspend processing of personal information at any time to sususoft.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">2.According to Article 41 Paragraph 1 of the Enforcement Decree of the 「Personal Information Protection Act」 to sususoft, the exercise of the rights pursuant can be done by in writing, e-mail, facsimile transmission such as FAX, and etc. And sususoft will take action without delay.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">3.The exercise of rights pursuant to Paragraph 1 may be done through an agent such as the legal representative of the information subject or a person who has been delegated. In this case, you must submit a power of attorney in the form of Attachment No. 11 of the “Personal Information Processing Method Notice (No. 2020-7)”.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">4.The rights of the information subject may be restricted in accordance with Article 35 (4) and Article 37 (2) of the 「Personal Information Protection Act」 for requesting access to and suspension of processing of personal information.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">5.The request for correction or delettion of personal information cannot be requested if the personal information is specified as a collection target in other laws.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">6.sususoft will confirmed the person who made the request is a legitimate agent according to the information subject\'s right or himself. To request for reading, correction or deletion, request for cancelation of processing, and ETC.</span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 4 (Creating clause of personal information to be processed)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&lt; sususoft &gt; is handling the following personal information items.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">● &nbsp; &lt; Homepage membership registration and management &gt;<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">● &nbsp; Required information: email, mobile phone number, password Q&amp;A, password, login ID, date of birth, name, credit card information, bank account information, service use record, access log, cookie, access IP information, payment record, legal representative name , legal representative home phone number, legal representative home address, and legal representative mobile phone number<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">● &nbsp;Optional information: email, mobile phone number, password Q&amp;A, password, login ID, gender, date of birth, name, credit card information, bank account information, service use record, access log, cookie, access IP information, payment record, court Representative\'s name, legal representative\'s home phone number, legal representative\'s home address, and legal representative\'s mobile phone number<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 5 (Destruction of personal information)</span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">‌<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp;1. &lt; sususoft &gt; destroys the personal information without delay when the personal information becomes unnecessary, such as the elapse of the personal information retention period or achievement of the processing purpose.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">2.If the personal information retention period agreed by the information subject has elapsed or the personal information needs to be kept in accordance with other laws despite the achievement of the purpose of processing, move the personal information to a separate database (DB) or change the storage location to preserve it.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">A.Legal Basis<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">B.List of personal information to be preserved: Bank account information, transaction date<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">3.The procedure and method of personal information destruction are as follows.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">A.The procedure of destruction<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&lt; sususoft &gt; will selects the personal information that reason for destruction occurred, and destroy the personal information with the approval from the personal information protection officer of &lt; sususoft &gt;.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">B.Method of destruction<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Information in the form of electronic files will be used a technical method that cannot reproduce the record. Personal information printed on paper will be shredded with a shredder or destroyed through incineration.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 6 (Measures to ensure the safety of personal information)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">1. &lt; sususoft &gt; destroys the personal information without delay when the personal information becomes unnecessary, such as the elapse of the personal information retention period or achievement of the processing purpose.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">2.If the personal information retention period agreed by the information subject has elapsed or the personal information needs to be kept in accordance with other laws despite the achievement of the purpose of processing, move the personal information to a separate database (DB) or change the storage location to preserve it.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">A.Legal Basis<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">B.List of personal information to be preserved: Bank account information, transaction date<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">3.The procedure and method of personal information destruction are as follows.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">A.The procedure of destruction<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&lt; sususoft &gt; will selects the personal information that reason for destruction occurred, and destroy the personal information with the approval from the personal information protection officer of &lt; sususoft &gt;.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">B.Method of destruction<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Information in the form of electronic files will be used a technical method that cannot reproduce the record. Personal information printed on paper will be shredded with a shredder or destroyed through incineration.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 7 (Matters concerning the installation, operation and rejection of automatic personal information collection devices)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">sususoft does not use \'cookies\' that store the information subject\'s usage information and call it from time to time.</span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 8 (Personal Information Protection Officer)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">1.sususoft is responsible for overall handling of personal information, and designates a person in charge of personal information protection as follows for complaint handling and damage relief of information subjects related to personal information processing.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">●Personal Information Protection Officer<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">●Name: Taekyu Kim<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">● &nbsp; &nbsp;Position: CEO<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">● &nbsp; &nbsp;Contacts: susu@sususoft.com<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">※You will be directed to the department in charge of personal information protection.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ● &nbsp; &nbsp;Department of personal information protection<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ● &nbsp; &nbsp;Department name: Game development and service operation Dept<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ● &nbsp; &nbsp;Manager: Sangki Yun &nbsp; &nbsp;Contact: sangkiyun@sususoft.com,<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">2.While using the service of sususoft, the information subject can inquire about all personal information protection related inquiries, complaint handling, damage relief, etc. to the person in charge of personal information protection and the department in charge. sususoft will answer and handle the inquiries of the information subject without delay.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 9 (Request for browsing personal information)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">The information subject may file a request for access to personal information in accordance with Article 35 of the Personal Information Protection Act to the following departments. &lt; sususoft &gt; will make every effort to promptly process the personal information access request of the information subject.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;● &nbsp; &nbsp;Reception and processing department of personal information access request<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;● &nbsp; &nbsp;Department name: Game development and service operation Dept<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;● &nbsp; &nbsp;Manager: Sangki Yun &nbsp; &nbsp;Contact: sangkiyun@sususoft.com,<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\">Article 10 (Remedies for Infringement of Rights)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">The information subject may apply for dispute resolution or consultation in order to receive relief from personal information infringement, through Personal Information Dispute Mediation Committee, Korea Internet &amp; Security Agency, and Personal Information Infringement Report Center. In addition, for other personal information infringement reports and consultations, please contact the following organizations.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">1. Personal Information Dispute Mediation Committee: (+82)1833-6972(www.kopico.go.kr)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">2. Personal Information Infringement Report Center : (+82)118 (privacy.kisa.or.kr)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">3. Supreme Prosecutor\'s Office : (+82) 1301 (www.spo.go.kr)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">4. National Police Agency : (+82) 182 (ecrm.cyber.go.kr)<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">The head of a public institution responds to a request pursuant to Article 35 (Perusal of Personal Information), Article 36 (Correction/Deletion of Personal Information), and Article 37 Suspension of Personal Information Processing, etc.) of the 「Personal Information Protection Act」 A person whose rights or interests have been infringed due to a disposition or omission taken may file an administrative appeal in accordance with the Administrative Appeals Act.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">※ For more information on administrative appeals, please refer to the website of the Central Administrative Appeals Committee (www.simpan.go.kr).<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"></span><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word;\"><font color=\"#737373\" face=\"Droid Serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">Article 11 (Change of Privacy Policy)</span></font><br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">This Privacy Policy will be effective from 30th November 2021.<br style=\"word-break: break-word;\">The previous Privacy Policy can be found below.</span><br></p>','2022-04-26 12:54:45'),
